        <td bgcolor='black' valign=top width='100' nowrap><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'><b>Tauruse</b></font></td>
        <td bgcolor='black' valign='top' width='100%'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Rather than constantly complain, a discussion on what is and what is not enough playing time to enjoy EverQuest might prove more productive.  </P><P>To start I hope we can all agree that depending on your stage in life, in a stereo typical world, the amount of casual time a man (I’m a man I won’t try and speak for others) looks like an inverse bell curve or conversely a bell curve of responsibilities to be met.  </P><P>Weekends are out.  I spend time with my children (If you think leveling is hard, try building character in to a person) and wife on the weekends and after the children go to bed I spend time with my wife (No, she will not play EQ because she “doesn’t have the time.”.    Weekends are also filled with the mundane chores of taking care of the lawn and house and cars.  Toss in the shopping, laundry, and other chores as well.  The number of things to be done can be staggering.</P><P>Of course, weeknights are pretty much out, after work I have to get home and either help with dinner or maybe I get lucky and just have to eat dinner and help cleanup.  After dinner the children need attention, you know the whole learning thing and the constant drive to make them feel loved as much as possible, we do reading, writing, math and some playing.  Then of course we do baths for the children and put them to bed with a short story for each.  By now it is at least after nine and my wife and I watch the news and I listen to her (BTW, that’s a great piece of advice.).  By the time the news is over it’s ten thirty-ish and I get some sleep.  The routine starts all over again at five in the morning.</P><P>At 37 with a wife and three children 8, 6 and 2 a full time job that requires at least 10 hour days, a home, a car and a retired father (these things all require attention), I don’t have a lot of free time. How much free time do I have?  Well, as I’ve said in another thread I’ve had about three hours this month to log on and play.  EQ isn’t like surfing the Internet.  I can walk away from this board for an entire day and I won’t lose any valuable time investment.  While, walking away from your (active logged in) avatar for a day would of course lead to dire consequences. </P><P>If I can get an hour in a week, I am kicking some serious ass from my perspective.  </P><P>So for me casual is very limited playing time.  For other people depending on where they fall on the “responsibility” bell curve how much free time do they have?  I don’t know, you tell me, if you’d be so kind.    </P><P><BR><center>The 3yr old level 51 Necro...<img src=icon_smile_clown.gif border=0 align=middle><BR>The caster balancing is going really well for us Necromancers.<BR><font color=blue>Think about the word THONG.</font id=blue><BR></center></font></td>
