        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Tauruse, I hear you, man.  EQ can and in some ways is a huge time-sink.  </P><P>Can a casual gamer (one that has 1-2 hours a night) really play EQ?</P><P>Yes, but with limitations.    </P><P>As a necro, you've at least picked something you can solo with, that's a start.  </P><P>Leveling...Necro's can go non-stop for an hour or two to get exp, that's easy solo.  Grouping, is good, but hard to do for such short amounts of time.  </P><P>Friends, when you make EQ friends, unless they play the same limited hours as you, it's difficult to stay in the level range of them.  </P><P>Raiding...well with an occasional night to "EQ" yes, you can raid, but not very often, that puts all the uber gear out of reach.</P><P>Quests, well some are good, some are bad.</P><P>One of the really good things you can do in limited time is play the market game, but that's not really "playing EQ", that's playing the EQ economy.  A couple of guildies are just starting to play their level 40 characters after spending a lot of time doing the market thing.  They have incredible gear for such low levels and a bank that makes mine look like pitance.</P><P>On many levels it would be easier and more fun for you to have an affair then play EQ.  Sadly, I'm guessing you'll have to sacrifice sleep in order to really get in and play EQ.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95266" target="_blank">Kuotat Smith</a><BR><s>Warlock</s> Witch<BR>Mithaniel Marr</font></td>
