        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Alaaraaf</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Is casual a relative term?</P><P>I think it pretty much has to be.  I play a whole lot more than you do and <b>still</b> consider myself to be a casual player.  <i>(Maybe twenty hours, some weeks.  Might go a coupla weeks at a time without playing at all.  Have been playing for a little over a year and have had two blocks of about two months, during which I haven't played at all.)</i>  I'm a student, so in general, I tend to play during holidays and late at night, after my girlfriend goes to bed.  I don't play when she's about, simply 'cos it'd be downright rude to sit and ignore her, to play EQ.  <i>(From time to time, I'll finish something I'm in the middle of, if she's about.  Corpse runs and the like, but that's about it.)</i></P><P>There is a vast disparity in what is available to a player who can commit hours at a time and someone who can't.  <i>(I'm sure you recall being told you know fuck all, by Sallymanders, for being only level fifty-one.  In fact, he went so far as to say that even being level sixty <b>and</b> in one of his server's best guilds for a long time wasn't adequate to experience the best of what Norrath has to offer!)</i>  I regularly play thirty minute, or one hour chucks and there's not a whole lot ya can do with that.  I still have fun, don't get me wrong about that, but there's not much room to argue the point over this.</P><P>It's a bit tricky, at the same time to say that someone who plays Everquest like it's their job shouldn't have access to better experiences and loot than someone who plays casually.  That's inevitable.  The vast gulf between what is available to the elite and that available for the majority of players seems a little off to me, but what can ya do?  I think it's something that might've benefitted both Verant and the players, if it was better thought out, but it's pretty much certain there's naff all that can be done to fix it now!</P><P>I'd be willing to argue that the minimum time to enjoy Everquest is pretty low, with a coupla conditions.  Firstly, you have to accept that you'll level slowly and your gear will never shine.  I don't mind this.  I'd like to have the time to get some extra levels and I'd <b>love</b> to be able to quest the Epic, but these things just ain't happening in the short term.  Also, you have to remember, the interface for Everquest is a travesty against design and makes getting into the game when you start <b>much</b> harder than is justifiable!  The second thing is you have to accept that a big ass chunk of the game world will be barred to you.  At level fifty-three I've been to a coupla minor raids.  I just don't have the time for huge long raids.  <i>(Which, obviously, puts a big dent in any hope of seeing the Epic!  *Sigh*)</i>  There're lotsa things I can do, but five hour raids are just not an option.  Much less these multi-day things, like PoA!!!</P><P>As for the responsibility thing?  I'm pretty low on the bell curve.  I have a responsibility not to ignore my girlfriend and to do reasonably well at school.  <i>(One more year and I'm lookin' for a job and lotsa loot.  More responsibility then!)</i>  No kids, no morgage, no job, no lawn.  </P><P>Still, casual crap, or otherwise, I whacked the corrupted cyclops in OoT last night solo, outta sheer badness, 'cos the Druid who needed it's drop annoyed me.  <i>(He was lookin' for guildees to come kill it.  I and one other person volunteered and he said we'd just get killed, if we didn't have healers and meatshields!  Bah!)</i>  He got his drop and I got to plague him on /gu, for doubting the awesome might of a smart-arse Necromancer.  <i>(Got summoned at the beginning.  Thought for a moment that I was gonna get waxed after annoyin' him!  *Grin*)</i>  Gonna start on the Phenocryst's focus tonight also, since I only need to assemble a group at the end of it.  </P><P>I think playing a class that can't solowould be pretty horrific, within any real time constraints, though!</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
